      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 85: Changing the ponderated loss initial value from the previous effective 10% static default to 0% materially changes bitrate adaptation behavior, not only first-RTCP congestion signaling. With the old value, early audio bitrate adaptation was conservative; now initial loss smoothing can under-report early loss. If the goal is only to avoid firing the audio-to-video callback on startup, keep the previous smoothing seed and gate the congestion callback until at least one real RTCP sample has been processed.",
      "revId": "4698d284121939cc873d37f2e7eec5d9cfcaad87",
