      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 636: The simulator drops RTP after libav/FFmpeg has produced the packet but returns buf_size as if the write succeeded. That is useful for synthetic loss, but it also means upstream send-rate/accounting sees successful transmission and cannot distinguish simulated drops from real network sends. Please document this explicitly in the SocketPair API or expose simulator stats to tests that assert QoS behavior, otherwise tests may accidentally validate sender accounting instead of actual simulated delivery.",
